summary:
Entrepreneurial professional with twenty years experience at the intersection of supply chain, finance and impact. President at AFEX, Africa's fastest growing company. Independent director, board member and advisor. Expert in international trade of soft commodities. Equally at home in Europe and Africa.

I am passionate about food and agribusiness, and on a mission to redefine the food system at scale. I am committed to empower 10 million people through employment, training and market access, and facilitate $1billion for sustainable agrifood.

Adding value through understanding, focus and solutions in complex value chain realities. Based on professional experience with over 250 organizations in over 50 countries, I speak the language of corporates and entrepreneurs, finance and impact, Europe and Africa. I believe that creating real value can always be profitable. I never compromise on people, integrity and quality.

Open to supervisory and non-executive director roles in impact investing and agrifood.
